{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BsZjH2f2aK6C8z6aMUxLof","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n     2→\n     3→### Session 37 — state corruption fix #21, no-op (2026-03-27T15:59Z)\n     4→\n     5→- **State corruption fix #21**: Same pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 reverted to `review`, epic-16 reverted to `backlog`, done count dropped from 74 to 70.\n     6→- Evidence: all 4 stories have proof documents in `verification/` and \"verified and done\" git commits.\n     7→- Fixed: restored 4 stories to `done`, updated sprint totals (70→74), set epic-16 to `done`.\n     8→- **Root cause unchanged**: Ralph stale in-memory state overwrites. 21st occurrence.\n     9→- **No actionable stories remain**: All 74 stories across 17 epics are `done`. Sprint is complete.\n    10→\n    11→## Token Report\n    12→- Total tool calls: ~12\n    13→- By tool: Bash: 3, Read: 4, Edit: 5\n    14→- Files read: 4 unique, 5 total reads\n    15→- Redundant operations: None — efficient fix of known recurring issue\n    16→\n    17→### Session 34 — state corruption fix #18, no-op (2026-03-27T15:48Z)\n    18→\n    19→- **State corruption fix #18**: Same recurring pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 at `review` in sprint-state.json, epic-16 at `backlog`. All 4 stories confirmed done via `git log` (commits with \"verified and done\") and proof documents exist in `verification/`.\n    20→- Fixed: restored 4 stories to `done`, updated sprint totals (70→74), set epic-16 to `done` in sprint-status.yaml.\n    21→- **Root cause unchanged**: Ralph process with stale in-memory state continues to overwrite. This has been the same issue since session 31+. The fix deployed in session 22 (`registerStory` guard) prevents new phantoms but doesn't prevent ralph from reverting statuses of existing stories.\n    22→- **No actionable stories remain**: All 74 stories across 17 epics are `done`. Sprint is complete.\n    23→\n    24→## Token Re